/*!
\page bobui-add-binary-resources.html
\ingroup cmake-commands-bobuicore

\title bobui_add_binary_resources
\keyword bobui6_add_binary_resources

\summary {Creates an RCC file from a list of BobUI resource files.}

\include cmake-find-package-core.qdocinc

\cmakecommandsince 5.10

\section1 Synopsis

\badcode
bobui_add_binary_resources(target file1.qrc [file2.qrc ...]
                        [DESTINATION ...]
                        [OPTIONS ...])
\endcode

\versionlessCMakeCommandsNote bobui6_add_binary_resources()

\section1 Description

Adds a custom \c target that compiles BobUI resource files into a binary \c{.rcc}
file.

\section1 Arguments

\c{DESTINATION} sets the path of the generated \c{.rcc} file. The default is
\c{${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/${target}.rcc}.

You can set additional \c{OPTIONS} that should be added to the \c{rcc} calls.
You can find possible options in the \l{rcc}{rcc documentation}.

\section1 Examples

\snippet cmake-macros/examples.cmake bobui_add_binary_resources
*/
